<p>The existence of similarities among the <a href="/wiki/Deity" title="Deity">deities</a> and religious practices of the <a href="/wiki/Indo-Europeans" title="Indo-Europeans" class="mw-redirect">Indo-European</a> (IE) peoples allows glimpses of a common <b><a href="/wiki/Proto-Indo-Europeans" title="Proto-Indo-Europeans">Proto-Indo-European</a> (PIE) religion and mythology</b>. Reconstruction is based on the <a href="/wiki/Comparative_method" title="Comparative method">comparative method</a>. Archaeological evidence is difficult to match to any specific culture in the period of early Indo-European culture in the <a href="/wiki/Chalcolithic" title="Chalcolithic" class="mw-redirect">Chalcolithic</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
